The paper deals with modeling a communication game between human agents using prospect theory models, which involves decision making under uncertainty. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of prospect theory models for decision making suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of the effects of weight functions on optimal communication strategies suggests that the paper could also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
